I"'<p>By <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/poverty-amid-plenty-predicts-health-and-crime">limiting poor conditions to a lower class</a>, stratified societies sequester mortality to specific strata. This enables an elitist form of <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/how-can-routine-cell-replacement-permit-psychological-continuity">continuity</a>, yet less stratified societies might also <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/parallel-distributed-processing-is-resilient-and-efficient">use redundancy to their advantage</a>.</p>
